ory, raising new questions concerning the dialectics of assimilation. In addition to that, the volume sheds light on thinkers and debates that hitherto have not been accorded full scholarly attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aJewish philosophyzGermany. 0aJudaism and philosophy. 0aJudaismzGermanyxHistory. 4aDeutsch-Jüdische Geschichte. 4aJüdische Geistesgeschichte. 4aJüdische Philosophie. 4aModernes Judentum. 4aReligionsphilosphie. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  aGerman-Jewish History.  aJewish Intellectual History.  aJewish Philosophy.  aModern Judaism.  aReligious Philosophy.1 aBatnitzky, Leora F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiemann, Asher D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraiterman, Zachary J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, Cass, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoetschel, Willi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Peter E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottlieb, Michah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHollander, Dana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKajon, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKavka, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKepnes, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLazier, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagid, Shaul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Benjamin, 